 East London - The Buffalo City Metro’s payment building in the East London CBD, and Beacon Bay had to be closed on Wednesday, due to Covid-19 positive cases. "The Municipality will follow the Covid-19 protocols that include deep cleansing and decontamination of the building before employees can report back for duty," it advised residents. "The offices in EL CBD will reopen on 19 June whilst in Beacon Bay it will be 22 June. "All staff working at these buildings have been informed that they are now required to work remotely and / or from home. "This is precautionary measures to the safeguard the safety of employees as per requirements set out by the Department of Health." The Metro said that it is doing everything it can to bring the situation to normal. "Customers who would like to make enquiries in respect of their accounts can do so through the institutions Call Centre in the following number is 086 111 3017." It said, alternatively, payment of accounts can be done in the easypay outlets such as the following: • Shoprite• Pick ’n’ pay• Woolworths• Pepor• Standard bank "Please note that a statement of the account will be required if the customer chooses to make a payment in the above outlets," the Metro advised. "We apologize for any inconvenience caused by this." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 